<?xml version="1.0"?>
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui='http://www.jythongwt.uibinderxsd.com'
	xmlns:g='http://www.jythongwt.uibinderxsd.com' xmlns:p='http://www.jythongwt.uibinderxsd.com'
	xmlns:i='http://www.jythongwt.uibinderxsd.com' xmlns='http://www.jythongwt.uihtml.com'>

   <ui:style type="com.vaadin.polymer.demo.client.sampler.Sampler.Style">
        @external .iron-selected, .paper-toast-open, .horizontal-section;

        .toolbar {
            background: #00796B !important;
        }
        .toolbar > div {
           justify-content: center;
        }
        .toolbar > div {
           padding: 0px !important;
           bottom: -4px !important;
        }

        .toolbar paper-fab {
           margin: 5px;
        }

        [drawer] {
            background-color: #ffffff !important;
        }

        .category {
            background: #009688;
            font-size: large;
            color: #f1f1f1;
        }
        .item {
            padding-left: 50px;
            font-size: 15px;
            min-height: 37px !important;
            color: #009688;
        }
        .list {
            background-color: #F5F4F4;
        }
        .list .iron-selected {
            background-color: #CDE5E3;
        }
        .list paper-item {
            border-top: solid 1px rgba(245, 245, 245, 0.6);

        }
        .buttons paper-material {
            font-size: 13 !important;
            margin: 0px;
            text-transform: none !important;
        }
        .current {
            overflow: hidden;
            text-overflow: ellipsis;
            white-space: nowrap;
            font-size: 150%;
            margin-left: 20px;
            margin-right: 15px;
        }
        paper-header-panel {
            z-index: auto !important;
        }
        .paper-toast-open {
            z-index: 10;
        }
        .panel {
            padding: 20px;
        }
        paper-item {
            cursor: pointer;
            oveflow: hidden;
            position: relative;
        }
        .title {
           font-size: 135%;
           text-align: center;
           padding: 5px;
        }
        @external .tall;
        .toolbar.tall {
           height: 108px !important;
           padding: 0 !important;
        }
        .toolbar.tall #bottomBar {
           height: 50px !important;
        }
        .source pre {
           font-size: 12px;
           line-height: 13px;
           background-color: #CDE5E3;
           padding: 10px;
        }
        .source-buttons {
           background-color: #CDE5E3;
           height: 45px;
           padding: 0px 0px 0px 30px;
           color: #009688;
        }
        .source-buttons iron-icon {
           margin: 0px 0px 4px 4px;
           width: 14px;
        }
        paper-header-panel[mode="waterfall-tall"]  #mainContainer {
          overflow: auto;
        }
        .hidden {
           opacity: 0;
        }

        .horizontal-section {
          min-width: 400px;
        }
    </ui:style>

    <g:HTMLPanel addStyleNames="{style.hidden}">
       <style is='custom-style'>
        .iconpolymer {
           --paper-fab-background: var(--paper-purple-500);
        }
        .icongwt {
           --paper-fab-background: var(--paper-red-500);
        }
        .iconvaadin {
           --paper-fab-background: var(--paper-light-blue-500);
        }
        /* Fix for https://github.com/PolymerElements/paper-menu/issues/31 */
        paper-item iron-icon,
        paper-item span {
            pointer-events: none;
        }
       </style>

<!--         <i:IronAjax fieldid="ironAjax" url="gwtPolymerDemo/contacts.json" auto="true"/> -->

        <p:PaperDrawerPanel fieldid="drawerPanel">
            <div drawer="">
                <p:PaperHeaderPanel mode="seamed">
                    <p:PaperToolbar addStyleNames="{style.toolbar} ">
                    <p:PaperFab fieldid="logo3" icon="polymer" attributes="mini url:http://polymer-project.org" addStyleNames="iconpolymer"></p:PaperFab>
                    <p:PaperFab fieldid="logo2" src="img/gwt.png" attributes="mini url:http://gwtproject.org" addStyleNames="icongwt"></p:PaperFab>
                    <p:PaperFab fieldid="logo1" icon="vaadin-icons:vaadin-v" attributes="mini url:http://vaadin.com/gwt" addStyleNames="iconvaadin"></p:PaperFab>
                    </p:PaperToolbar>
                    <g:FlowPanel fieldid="listPanel" addStyleNames="{style.list}"/>
                </p:PaperHeaderPanel>
            </div>
            <div main="">
                <p:PaperHeaderPanel mode="waterfall-tall">
                    <p:PaperToolbar addStyleNames="{style.toolbar}" >
                        <p:PaperIconButton icon="menu" attributes="paper-drawer-toggle" />
                        <span fieldid="currentLabel" class="{style.current}"></span>
                        <span class="flex"></span>
                        <p:PaperButton fieldid="help" addStyleNames="{style.buttons}"><i:IronIcon icon="help"/>About</p:PaperButton>
                        <div class="{style.source-buttons} bottom flex">
                            <span>VIEW SOURCE: </span>
                            <p:PaperButton fieldid="javaButton" addStyleNames="{style.buttons}">.java<i:IronIcon icon="launch"/></p:PaperButton>
                            <p:PaperButton fieldid="xmlButton" addStyleNames="{style.buttons}">.ui.xml<i:IronIcon icon="launch"/></p:PaperButton>
                        </div>
                    </p:PaperToolbar>
                    <g:HTMLPanel fieldid="content" addStyleNames="{style.panel} fit"/>
                </p:PaperHeaderPanel>
            </div>
        </p:PaperDrawerPanel>

        <p:PaperDialog fieldid="about" modal="true" >
          <p:PaperDialogScrollable>
            <h2>About GWT-Polymer-Elements</h2>
             <p>
               GWT-Polymer-Elements is a library developed in Vaadin Labs. It allows to use Polymer Elements in GWT projects.
             </p>
             <p>
               The source code of the library has been enterely generated with Vaadin gwt-api-generator, an utility able to inspect polymer webcomponents and emit GWT java files.
             </p>
             <p>
               Since GWT, Gwt-Api-Generator and Gwt-Polymer-Elements are Apache Licensed, and Polymer Elements is BSD Licensed, you have a full open-source stack to develop modern Ajax applications in Java.
             </p>
             <p>
               The project does not maintain any java code (except the demo) and it is actually a 'node' script able to download components, generate java wrappers, and eventually compile and upload generated .jar to maven repos.
             </p>
             <p>
               The main goal of the library is to reuse in GWT external components utilising modern techniques like 'JsInterop' and 'Hydrolysis', instead of the tedious classic way: learn 3rd party JS APIs and write dozens of java classes by hand.
             </p>
             <p>
               Web components is a technology based on new standards, hence it is thought in the present for the future.
               We are aware about performance issues in browsers not already implementing them, but browser vendors would finally solve it.
             </p>
             <p>
               Anyway, we believe that it is worth to start experimenting and learning web components sooner, and contributing with the growing community around these new trends.
             </p>
            <div class="buttons">
                <p:PaperButton attributes="dialog-dismiss"  raised="true">OK</p:PaperButton>
            </div>
          </p:PaperDialogScrollable>
        </p:PaperDialog>

        <p:PaperDialog fieldid="source" modal="true" addStyleNames="{style.source}">
            <h2 fieldid="sourceTitle">Source</h2>
            <p:PaperDialogScrollable>
               <paper-material elevation="3">
                 <pre fieldid="sourceContent"></pre>
               </paper-material>
            </p:PaperDialogScrollable>
            <div class="buttons">
                <p:PaperButton attributes="dialog-dismiss"  raised="true">OK</p:PaperButton>
            </div>
        </p:PaperDialog>

    </g:HTMLPanel>
    
</ui:UiBinder>

